# 8. 少しあたたかい雪

Shizuku: *Sigh* Such a shame...
Mafuyu: Hehe. Hinomori, I think you're being too hard on yourself.
Shizuku: But I missed my last shot...
Mafuyu: Then, let's have another contest sometime.
Shizuku: What?
Mafuyu: This one ended in a draw...
Mafuyu: But I'll win next time.
Shizuku: Yes, let's...! And I promise to do my best then!
Mafuyu: At the same time... This place has a very different feel to it when it's snowing.
Shizuku: I agree. And no one else is here... It's almost like we're in a dream of some sort.
Shizuku: Speaking of which, I often used to make snow rabbits when I was little.
Mafuyu: Snow rabbits?
Shizuku: Yes. Because Shii always really liked it whenever I did.
Shizuku: Oh, this might be just enough snow... All you have to do is round some up into a ball and...
Shizuku: For the eyes...we can use these bamboo berries, and some leaves for the ears. And there you are. A snow rabbit.
Mafuyu: Hehe. It's very cute...
Mafuyu: At the same time, it's also a little sad that it's going to melt when the sun comes out...
Shizuku: Yes... Shii used to say the same thing.
Shizuku: But it's not all bad.
Mafuyu: Huh?
Shizuku: The memory of having made this snow rabbit will remain.
Shizuku: It may be physically gone... But as long as you don't forget, it'll persist as a precious piece of your past.
Mafuyu: As long as I don't forget...
Mafuyu: Do you really believe that...?
Shizuku: I can't say for sure, but want to believe it's true...
Mafuyu: I see...
Shizuku: So, I'd like it if you could remember what we did today...
Mafuyu: What?
Shizuku: I'm sure that there are already plenty of people around you who are willing to give you their support.
Shizuku: But I'd like it if you could remember that I'm also there for you.
Mafuyu: Thank you...
Shizuku: (Huh...? Just now. She seemed a little...)
Mafuyu: Anyway, it's starting to get dark, so let's head home.
Shizuku: Oh, right. We should...
Shizuku: Eep!!!
Mafuyu: H-Hinomori?! Is everything okay? Are you hurt?
Shizuku: I-I'm sorry. I slipped on the ice... That was so scary...!
Shizuku: Fortunately, I didn't get hurt so... Oh no!
Mafuyu: What's wrong?
Shizuku: My umbrella... I bent it... What do I do...?
Mafuyu: Oh, you're right. It probably won't open now...
Mafuyu: So, why don't we walk to the station together? We should both be able to fit under my umbrella.
Shizuku: Really? Thank you so much, Asahina...!
Mafuyu: You're welcome. Please, come in.
Shizuku: Then, if you don't mind.
Mafuyu: Oh. Hehe...
Shizuku: Huh? Is something the matter, Asahina?
Mafuyu: It's just... Hinomori, there's some snow on your face. Hehehe...
Shizuku: Th-There is? Oh dear...
Mafuyu: Just give me one second. I'll get it with my handkerchief...
Mafuyu: There. All gone...
Shizuku: Oh... My hands are so cold. I guess I was outside for a fairly long time.
Shizuku: And yet...
Shiho: Oh, Shizuku, you're home.
Shizuku: Oh, Shii. Yes, I am.
Shiho: Mom said we're having curry for dinner tonight, so she was wondering if you could help peel the... Hm?
Shiho: Did something good happen to you today...?
Shizuku: Oh, you noticed...?! But I didn't say anything! You're like a mind reader, Shii!
Shiho: I'm pretty sure anyone would've noticed. I mean, your grin sort of gave it all away...
Shiho: So, what happened?
Shizuku: Oh, so...! Um... It's a bit of a long story, but...
Shizuku: I was able to give back a little today...
Shiho: I see. Good for you...
Mother's Voice: Shiho! Shizuku! Mind helping me with these?
Shizuku: Oh... Yes! We'll be right there!
Shizuku: Let's go, Shii! We can talk more in the kitchen!
